data.name: Gateway of India
data.description: A remarkable monument built during the British rule in India. It is a huge basalt arch 26 meters high. Very impressing sight, that you should not miss.

data.name: Colaba Causeway Market
data.description: A street market area. If you want to see busy exotic market, this is the place. You can buy here various jewelry or other souvenirs.

data.name: Chhatrapati Shivaji International (BOM)
data.address:
Chhatrapati Shivaji International Airport
Mumbai 400 099
India

data.name: Chor Bazaar Market
data.description: If you like exotic flea markets this place will amaze you, it is real Indian culture. You can buy here the best souvenirs.

data.name: Shree Siddhivinayak Ganapati Temple
data.description: A unique Hindu temple dedicated to the god Ganesh. It has very rare architecture and during your trip to Mumbai you should not miss it.

data.name: Chhatrapati Shivaji Terminus
data.description: A historic railway station, that is on UNESCO list. Nowadays it serves as headquarters of the Central Railways. The building is magnificent.

data.name: Haji Ali Mosque and Tomb
data.description: A striking mosque and tomb of Muslim saint Haji. It is located on a peninsula and it is a sacred place for many Muslims.

data.name: Chowpatty Beach
data.description: One of the most popular beaches in India, it is great for sunset watching ant it is also a venue of religious Ganesh Chaturthi celebrations.

data.name: Marine Drive
data.description: One of the most popular boulevards along the shore of the sea. It is about 3 kilometers long and very suitable for walks or watching sunset.

data.name: Dhobi Ghat
data.description: A well-known open-air laundromat, that you may know from some movies. This place is the real face of Mumbai.

data.name: The Elephant Caves
data.description: A complex of caves located on the Elephant Island. The caves are decorated with carved sculptures. The sculptures are very impressing and look fabulous.

data.name: Fashion Street
data.description: A street with hundreds of fashion shops with clothes or jewelry. If you love shopping, you will spend here quite a long time.

data.name: Crawford Market
data.description: One of the most famous and largest public markets in Mumbai. It is a great place if you want to buy some souvenirs or you can just enjoy the atmosphere.

data.name: Leopold Café
data.description: A popular café, that is suitable both for lunch or dinner or for party in the evening.It has over 100 years of tradition.

data.name: Rajabai Clock Tower
data.description: An 85 meters height tower clock, that was designed by same architect as famous London Big Ben. It is decorated with beautiful stained glass windows.

data.name: Juhu Beach
data.description: A popular sandy beach, it is a great place for walks or sunset watching. However, water here is not clean so it is advised no to go to the water.

data.name: Mani Bhavan
data.description: A house, that is connected with Mahatma Gandhi and his political career. You can enjoy the museum, that is inside to find out more about this important person.

data.name: Hanging Gardens
data.description: This beautiful terraced gardens located on the Malabar Hill are great place if you want to relax after all day of sightseeing.

data.name: Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Vastu Museum
data.description: The main Mumbai museum that has an extensive collections of art, archaeological and natural history artifacts.

data.name: Flora Fountain
data.description: An exquisite Gothic revival fountain that is depicting the Roman goddess Flora. It looks really wonderful especially in the evening.

data.name: Mumbai Zoo
data.description: A remarkable zoo that shows many endangered species of animals. Especially elephants here are great and all kids will enjoy them.

data.name: Dharavi
data.description: If you want to see how real Mumbai slum looks like, visit this place. Lot of people living in small houses with garbage everywhere.

data.name: Kanheri Caves
data.description: A magnificent caves, not far from Mumbai. The whole complex is man-made and it dates back about 2000 years. It is carved in the rock and offers wonderful experience.

data.name: Nehru Science Centre
data.description: A huge interactive science complex, that provides unusual and rare expositions. You will learn many fascinating facts during the visit.

data.name: Mangaldas Market
data.description: A great place to buy some Indian clothing and textiles for fair price. It is very busy and crowded place.

data.name: Global Vipassana Pagoda
data.description: This amazing pagoda is one of the highlights of Mumbai. It serve as monument of peace and harmony. Do not miss the opportunity to admire it.

attribution.title: Motif on Global Vipassana Pagoda in Mumbai, India.
attribution.author: Joe Ravi

70x70.title: The Global Vipassana Pagoda under construction in Mumbai, India.

320x320.title: The Global Vipassana Pagoda under construction in Mumbai, India.

data.name: Mumbadevi Temple
data.description: A remarkable Hindu temple, that is dedicated to the goddess Mumbā. The temple and its surroundings have amazing atmosphere of tradition.

70x70.author: Vikas Amarjit Singh
70x70.title: Mumbadevi Temple, Bhuleshwar, Mumbai, Maharashtra, India

320x320.author: Vikas Amarjit Singh
320x320.title: Mumbadevi Temple, Bhuleshwar, Mumbai, Maharashtra, India

data.name: Jain Temple
data.description: One of the prettiest temples in Mumbai decorated with marvelous carvings. It is dedicated to Jainism, one of the Indian religions.

data.name: Walkeshwar Temple
data.description: This temple is dedicated to the Hindu god Shiva, it is usually peaceful except during the full moon. It has amazing atmosphere, so you should visit it.

data.name: Mount Mary Church
data.description: A Roman Catholic church dedicated to the Virgin Mary. It is decorated with delightful fresco paintings and statue of Virgin Mary.

attribution.title: This is picture taken at The Fatima Oratory, Mount Mary Bsilica, Bandra.
attribution.author: Marshall

data.name: Malabar Hill
data.description: One of the most exclusive neighborhoods in Mumbai. This place is worth of visit to feel the atmosphere of it.

data.name: Keneseth Eliyahoo Synagogue
data.description: An amazing sky-blue synagogue, that serves for local Jewish community. It is very interesting place to visit.

data.name: EsselWorld
data.description: A water theme park with lot of rides, slides and other attractions. It is a great place to spend summer day.

70x70.author: aanikett
70x70.title: Water Fountain by Roller Coaster, Essel World, Mumbai

320x320.author: aanikett
320x320.title: Water Fountain by Roller Coaster, Essel World, Mumbai

data.name: Mahalakshmi Temple
data.description: One of the best known temples in Mumbai, its interior has beautiful decoration featuring three Malakshmi idols Mahakali, Mahalakshmi, and Mahasaraswathi.

data.name: Powai Lake
data.description: This artificial lake is suitable for those who want to watch wild animals. You can see various kinds of birds or even crocodiles here.

data.name: Babulnath Temple
data.description: This ancient Shiva temple is dedicated to the lord Babul, one of the Shiva deities. You may know it from some Bollywood movies.

data.name: Taraporewala Aquarium
data.description: An indoor aquarium, that shows over 100 species of various marine and fresh water fish and also some fossils. The highlights are sharks and turtles.

data.name: Sanjay Gandhi National Park
data.description: This national park lies about two kilometers north of Mumbai, it is rich of various flora and fauna, so if you love nature, visit it.

attribution.title: Leopard at Sanjay Gandhi National Park Mini Zoo
attribution.author: Marcus334

data.name: Water Kingdom
data.description: An amusement park full of amazing water slides and rides. All kids will enjoy this place as well as adults.

data.name: Banganga Tank
data.description: An ancient water reservoir that is about 900 years old. The reservoir took place in some famous movies, so you may know it.

data.name: Museum Ship Vikrant
data.description: An aircraft carrier, that played important role in the Indo-Pakistan War of 1971. Nowadays it serves as a fascinating museum.

attribution.title: The ex-INS Vikrant as a museum ship in Mumbai.
attribution.author: Skyring

attribution.title: Aircraft elevator of INS Vikrant, decommissioned aircraft carrier of the Indian Navy.
attribution.author: AshLin

70x70.author: AshLin
70x70.title: Aircraft elevator of INS Vikrant, decommissioned aircraft carrier of the Indian Navy.

320x320.author: AshLin
320x320.title: Aircraft elevator of INS Vikrant, decommissioned aircraft carrier of the Indian Navy.

data.name: Film City
data.description: Huge complex comprising of movie studios as well as estates where many Bollywood films were shot. Take a tour and see it for yourself!

data.name: Pizza by the Bay
data.description: A restaurant with delicious pizza and delivery service. They also have Mediterranean cuisine, especially their pasta is great.

data.name: Cafe Basilico Bistro
data.description: A bistro that offers mainly European cuisine, their menu consists of Mediterranean dishes. It is very delicious and even vegetarians will be satisfied here.

data.name: Bluefrog Club
data.description: A very popular music venue with amazing atmosphere. It hosts famous international artists. If you want to party, this place is great.

data.name: Jehangir Art Gallery
data.description: A famous art gallery. It has wide selection of contemporary art by local artists, often available for purchase.

data.name: Priyadarshini Park
data.description: This park is suitable for various sports such as running or cycling. It is also an oasis of peace in the center of Mumbai.

data.name: St Thomas’ Cathedral
data.description: An Anglican cathedral built for growing British minority in 1837. The colonial atmosphere here is amazing.

data.name: Bombay Store
data.description: A large store with wide range of clothing, artifacts, decorations or stationery. It is at the airport, so you may visit it during waiting for your flight.

data.name: Cathedral of the Holy Name
data.description: A Roman catholic cathedral decorated with amazing fresco paintings. Its pipe organ has delightful sound.

data.name: Gorai Beach
data.description: A beautiful sandy beach, great for walks especially in the evening because of amazing sunset view. However it is not recommended for swimming.

data.name: Tower of Silence
data.description: A cemetery of Zoroastrian community in Mumbai. It is very interesting from outside however not accessible for tourists.

data.name: Cream Centre Veg Restaurant
data.description: A vegetarian restaurant, that offers dishes for those who do not like meat. However the highlight of this place is their ice cream. You have to taste it, it is really amazing.

data.name: Mumbai High Court
data.description: An elegant building built in the Neo-Gothic style. It is very impressive. You can walk inside to see the beautiful architecture.

data.name: Culture Curry Restaurant
data.description: If you want to taste real Indian curry then you must visit this restaurant. They also have wide menu for vegetarians.

data.name: University of Mumbai
data.description: A fascinating building, that is home to the University of Mumbai, it is built in neo-gothic style and it is really worth-seeing.

attribution.title: Library of University of Mumbai, India
attribution.author: Bernard Gagnon

70x70.author: Bernard Gagnon
70x70.title: Library of University of Mumbai, India

320x320.author: Bernard Gagnon
320x320.title: Library of University of Mumbai, India

data.name: Sheshrao Krushnarao Wankhede Stadium
data.description: A famous cricket stadium, the venue of world cricket championship in 2011.  Indians love cricket so if you want to enjoy the atmosphere visit one of the matches.

attribution.title: Wankhede Stadium during the first innings of the 2011 ICC World Cup Final between Sri Lanka and India.
attribution.author: G patkar

data.name: Goa Portuguesa Restaurant
data.description: This restaurant has an extensive menu of mainly Portuguese and Goa dishes. If you want to have great food this restaurant will satisfy you.

data.name: National Gallery of Modern Art
data.description: This intriguing spacious gallery offers thought-provoking expositions of modern art. One of highlights of their collection is work of Pablo Picasso.

70x70.author: Deepankar devesh
70x70.title: National gallery of modern art, mumbai

320x320.author: Deepankar devesh
320x320.title: National gallery of modern art, mumbai

data.name: The Four Fountains Spa
data.description: A spa chain, where you can get various types of massages and procedures. They also offer traditional Indian massages, so if you feel tired after traveling, you can relax here.

data.name: Swati Snacks
data.description: A modern cafeteria, that is perfect for breakfast. If you want to have some traditional but kind of unusual Indian dishes, this place is great for you.

data.name: National Centre for the Performing Arts
data.description: An artistic complex, where you can enjoy various performances such as music, dance or theater. For those who like classical music may be interesting Indian classical music orchestra.
data.original_name: National Centre for the Performing Arts

data.name: Mahalaxmi Racecourse
data.description: If you like horse races, this complex will offer you opportunity to enjoy them. The racecourse is over 100 years old and races here have long tradition.

data.name: Mocha Bar
data.description: The Arabian-style café is very popular with young people. It has amazing atmosphere with cozy and comfortable seating and world music playing.

data.name: Bhau Daji Lad Museum
data.description: The oldest museum in Mumbai, that houses rich collections of archaeological artifacts, maps and historical photos of Mumbai.

70x70.author: graphikamaal
70x70.title: Dr. Bhau Daji Lad Museum at Rani Baugh Bombay (Jijamata Udyan Mumbai)

320x320.author: graphikamaal
320x320.title: Dr. Bhau Daji Lad Museum at Rani Baugh Bombay (Jijamata Udyan Mumbai)

data.name: Jogger's Park
data.description: A small park that is often used by joggers, if you want to enjoy some jogging in Mumbai, this place is perfect.

data.name: Madh Island
data.description: It is in fact not an island but peninsula, that is notable for fishing villages and ruins of Madh fort. It offers amazing scenic view of Mumbai.

data.name: Shrujan Store
data.description: This store offers hand made intricate embroidery made in villages around Mumbai. Their clothing or wall hangings may be great souvenirs.

data.name: Cooperage Football Ground
data.description: A football stadium that is home to Mumbai F.C. and FC Air India. It is often a venue of international matches, so if you are football fan, you should see it.

attribution.title: A picture of the Eden Gardens stadium before the start of a match.

data.name: Monetary Museum
data.description: A museum focused on money. It has wide expositions of coins, banknotes and everything connected with money. Very intriguing place.

data.name: Mumbai Natural History Society
data.description: This institution provide bird watching trips, so if you are interested in ornithology or just admire these beautiful animals, take one of their trips.

data.name: Prithvi Theatre
data.description: This famous theater is venue of both Hindi and English plays. If you are drama enthusiast this place will offer you unusual plays.

data.name: Aarey Milk Colony
data.description: One of the most modern milk colonies in the world, it offers opportunity to take a excursion. There is also suitable area for picnics.

data.name: Chabad House
data.description: A center of Jewish community in Mumbai. This house was attacked by terrorists during the November 2008 Mumbai attacks.

data.name: Outbound Adventure Rafting Trips
data.description: Here you can buy rafting or canoeing trips. They will provide you with necessary equipment so you can enjoy your trip on water.

data.name: Drishti Sport Adventures
data.description: If you like adrenalin sports, you can buy wide range of them here. You can go jet skiing, snorkeling, windsurfing and many others.

data.name: Kashmir Government Arts Emporium
data.description: This place offers opportunity to buy various handicraft made northwestern region of Kashmir. It may be great place to buy some souvenirs.

data.name: Shivaji Park
data.description: An urban park, that had important role in Indian fight for freedom. Some of the important events took place here. It is decorated with statues commemorating this events.

data.name: Happy Planet
data.description: An indoor amusement park for small kids. It is full of various activities and attractions that all kids will love.
